				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8112002#post-4028654</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8112002/the-corncrake-of-destiny#post-4028654</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 19 Oct 2018 05:40:51 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Rigen</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2826105</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>several observed instances possess the ability to vocalize at a level higher than a sonic boom.</p> </blockquote> <p>I don't think you used &quot;sonic boom&quot; correctly here. Sonic boom is what happen if an object moves through air faster than the speed of sound, not a level of sound itself. A whip's crack is a sonic boom, even though it is relatively quiet compared to a fighter jet's boom when it goes supersonic.</p> <p>Also, agreeing with ARD. Eleanore is practically an adult among children, with Val being a slightly mature teenager that's not really helpful but at least not as obstructive as the other two. It just become really annoying to read.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
